{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775882734556,"sessionID":"ses_285243033ffe2PJh9gG9ejjgq0","part":{"id":"prt_d7adc06c80018BvDWqhr3JJ6MM","messageID":"msg_d7adbfc66001x5UfSHv1H4e1XG","sessionID":"ses_285243033ffe2PJh9gG9ejjgq0","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-af878c76051b448ea7b9b5a68718a7e8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-001/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-001/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-001 Delta Specification: CRD AgentRuntime 类型定义\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Define Go type definitions and Kubernetes CRD registration for the `AgentRuntime` custom resource in the `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` API group, including integration with the generated client-go library and proper API machinery support.\n6: \n7: ## Requirements\n8: \n9: ### Requirement: AgentRuntime type metadata and API group version\n10: \n11: The system SHALL define `AgentRuntime` as a Kubernetes custom resource with `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` API group, `v1alpha1` version, kind `AgentRuntime`, and resource plural `agentruntimes`.\n12: \n13: #### Scenario: Type metadata reflects GVR mapping\n14: - **GIVEN** a Kubernetes API server resolving the CRD type\n15: - **WHEN** the `TypeMeta` fields are inspected\n16: - **THEN** `APIVersion` is `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` and `Kind` is `AgentRuntime`\n17: \n18: #### Scenario: Resource plural matches client-go expectations\n19: - **GIVEN** a typed client for `AgentRuntime`\n20: - **WHEN** constructing a `GroupVersionResource` from the type\n21: - **THEN** resource name is `agentruntimes` in plural form\n22: \n23: ### Requirement: AgentRuntimeSpec structure with required fields\n24: \n25: The system SHALL define `AgentRuntimeSpec` struct with required fields: `PodTemplate` of type `*SandboxTemplate`, `SessionTimeout` of type `*metav1.Duration`, and `MaxSessionDuration` of type `*metav1.Duration`.\n26: \n27: #### Scenario: Spec requires pod template\n28: - **GIVEN** a new `AgentRuntime` object being created\n29: - **WHEN** the spec is populated\n30: - **THEN** `PodTemplate` must be non-nil and contains the sandbox pod template\n31: \n32: #### Scenario: Duration fields use metav1 types\n33: - **GIVEN** an existing `AgentRuntime` with timeouts configured\n34: - **WHEN** the spec is serialized to YAML\n35: - **THEN** `SessionTimeout` and `MaxSessionDuration` serialize as duration strings\n36: \n37: ### Requirement: AgentRuntimeStatus with conditions support\n38: \n39: The system SHALL define `AgentRuntimeStatus` struct with optional `Conditions` field of type `[]metav1.Condition` for tracking runtime state transitions.\n40: \n41: #### Scenario: Status conditions are optional\n42: - **GIVEN** a newly created `AgentRuntime` resource\n43: - **WHEN** status is initially empty\n44: - **THEN** resource creation succeeds without requiring conditions\n45: \n46: #### Scenario: Condition updates follow Kubernetes conventions\n47: - **GIVEN** a controller managing `AgentRuntime` lifecycle\n48: - **WHEN** transitioning between states (e.g., Creating → Running)\n49: - **THEN** conditions are added with appropriate types, reasons, and transition timestamps\n50: \n51: ### Requirement: AgentRuntimeList type for collection operations\n52: \n53: The system SHALL define `AgentRuntimeList` as a standard Kubernetes list type containing `[]AgentRuntime` items and standard list metadata.\n54: \n55: #### Scenario: List type supports pagination\n56: - **GIVEN** multiple `AgentRuntime` resources in a namespace\n57: - **WHEN** `List` operation is called with `ListOptions.Limit`\n58: - **THEN** response returns an `AgentRuntimeList` with `Continue` token when more items exist\n59: \n60: ### Requirement: Scheme registration for serialization\n61: \n62: The system SHALL register `AgentRuntime` and `AgentRuntimeList` types in the Kubernetes scheme for proper JSON/YAML serialization and deserialization.\n63: \n64: #### Scenario: YAML deserialization produces correct Go types\n65: - **GIVEN** a YAML file containing `kind: AgentRuntime` in the `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` API group\n66: - **WHEN** the YAML is decoded using the registered scheme\n67: - **THEN** an `AgentRuntime` struct instance is created with correct field mappings\n68: \n69: #### Scenario: List kind maps to AgentRuntimeList\n70: - **GIVEN** a YAML file containing `kind: AgentRuntimeList`\n71: - **WHEN** the YAML is decoded\n72: - **THEN** an `AgentRuntimeList` struct instance is created with items as `[]AgentRuntime`\n73: \n74: ### Requirement: CRD subresources support\n75: \n76: The system SHALL enable status subresource on `AgentRuntime` to allow independent updates to status without modifying spec.\n77: \n78: #### Scenario: Status update does not modify spec\n79: - **GIVEN** an existing `AgentRuntime` with both spec and status\n80: - **WHEN** a status-only update is performed via API server\n81: - **THEN** only status fields change and spec remains unmodified\n82: \n83: #### Scenario: Status and spec have independent versioning\n84: - **GIVEN** a controller updating status\n85: - **WHEN** status changes multiple times\n86: - **THEN** each status update increments `metadata.generation` independently of spec modifications\n87: \n88: ### Requirement: Default values for spec fields\n89: \n90: The system SHALL define kubebuilder markers to set default values: `SessionTimeout` defaults to `\"15m\"` and `MaxSessionDuration` defaults to `\"8h\"`.\n91: \n92: #### Scenario: Missing timeout fields receive defaults\n93: - **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntime` created without explicit timeout values\n94: - **WHEN** the resource is created via API\n95: - **THEN** `SessionTimeout` is set to `15m` and `MaxSessionDuration` to `8h` automatically\n96: \n97: #### Scenario: Explicit values override defaults\n98: - **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntime` created with custom timeout values\n99: - **WHEN** the resource is created\n100: - **THEN** the explicit values are preserved and defaults are not applied\n101: \n102: ### Requirement: OpenAPI validation for spec fields\n103: \n104: The system SHALL generate OpenAPI v3 schema for `AgentRuntime` to enable validation of field types, required fields, and constraints.\n105: \n106: #### Scenario: Required field validation\n107: - **GIVEN** a request creating `AgentRuntime` without required `PodTemplate`\n108: - **WHEN** the API server validates the request\n109: - **THEN** validation fails with error indicating `podTemplate` is required\n110: \n111: #### Scenario: Type validation for duration fields\n112: - **GIVEN** a request creating `AgentRuntime` with invalid duration format\n113: - **WHEN** the API server validates the request\n114: - **THEN** validation fails with error about invalid duration format\n115: \n116: ### Requirement: Print columns for kubectl readability\n117: \n118: The system SHALL configure additional printer columns for `kubectl get` output, including `Age` derived from `metadata.creationTimestamp`.\n119: \n120: #### Scenario: Age column displays correctly\n121: - **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntime` resource that was created 5 minutes ago\n122: - **WHEN** `kubectl get agentruntimes` is executed\n123: - **THEN** the Age column shows `5m` or equivalent time duration\n124: \n125: ### Requirement: CRD status storage optimization\n126: \n127: The system SHALL use status subresource to ensure status updates are stored efficiently and do not trigger spec reconciliation unnecessarily.\n128: \n129: #### Scenario: Frequent status updates\n130: - **GIVEN** a controller updating `AgentRuntime` status every 30 seconds\n131: - **WHEN** multiple status updates occur\n132: - **THEN** each update only writes to status subresource and does not trigger full reconciliation\n133: \n134: ### Requirement: Type registration in code-generation\n135: \n136: The system SHALL ensure `AgentRuntime` types are included in the client-go code-generation pipeline to produce typed clients, informers, and listers.\n137: \n138: #### Scenario: Typed client operations work\n139: - **GIVEN** a `Clientset` instance from generated client-go code\n140: - **WHEN** calling `client.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace).Create`\n141: - **THEN** the operation succeeds with proper type safety and returns an `AgentRuntime` pointer\n142: \n143: #### Scenario: Informer factory recognizes AgentRuntime\n144: - **GIVEN** a `SharedInformerFactory` for the runtime API group\n145: - **WHEN** `Runtime().V1alpha1().AgentRuntimes().Informer()` is called\n146: - **THEN** an informer watching `agentruntimes` resources is returned\n147: \n148: ### Requirement: JSON tag naming convention\n149: \n150: The system SHALL use camelCase JSON tags for all fields to match Kubernetes API conventions and client-go expectations.\n151: \n152: #### Scenario: JSON serialization uses camelCase\n153: - **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntime` struct populated with Go fields\n154: - **WHEN** serialized to JSON\n155: - **THEN** the JSON keys are camelCase (e.g., `podTemplate`, `sessionTimeout`, `maxSessionDuration`)\n156: \n157: ### Requirement: DeepCopy methods for safety\n158: \n159: The system SHALL implement `DeepCopy`, `DeepCopyInto`, `DeepCopyObject` methods for `AgentRuntime` to support safe copying in controllers.\n160: \n161: #### Scenario: DeepCopy creates independent instance\n162: - **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntime` instance with populated fields\n163: - **WHEN** `DeepCopy` is called\n164: - **THEN** the returned copy is independent and modifications to the copy do not affect the original\n165: \n166: ### Requirement: Validation markers for fields\n167: \n168: The system SHALL use kubebuilder validation markers to enforce constraints on spec fields where applicable.\n169: \n170: #### Scenario: Duration fields validate format\n171: - **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntime` with `SessionTimeout` set to invalid duration\n172: - **WHEN** the resource is submitted to the API server\n173: - **THEN** validation fails with error indicating invalid duration format\n174: \n175: ### Requirement: Label selector support for listing\n176: \n177: The system SHALL support standard Kubernetes label selectors when listing `AgentRuntime` resources.\n178: \n179: #### Scenario: Label selector filters results\n180: - **GIVEN** multiple `AgentRuntime` resources with different labels\n181: - **WHEN** `List` is called with a label selector matching a specific label\n182: - **THEN** only resources matching the selector are returned\n183: \n184: ### Requirement: Watch support for controller integration\n185: \n186: The system SHALL support watch operations on `AgentRuntime` resources to enable controllers to react to changes efficiently.\n187: \n188: #### Scenario: Watch events notify of changes\n189: - **GIVEN** a watch stream established on `AgentRuntime` resources\n190: - **WHEN** a new `AgentRuntime` is created\n191: - **THEN** the watch stream receives an ADDED event with the new resource\n\n(End of file - total 191 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-001 Delta Specification: CRD AgentRuntime 类型定义\n\n## Purpose\n\nDefine Go type definitions and Kubernetes CRD registration for the `AgentRuntime` custom resource in the `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` API group, including integration with the generated client-go library and proper API machinery support.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: AgentRuntime type metadata and API group version\n\nThe system SHALL define `AgentRuntime` as a Kubernetes custom resource with `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` API group, `v1alpha1` version, kind `AgentRuntime`, and resource plural `agentruntimes`.\n\n#### Scenario: Type metadata reflects GVR mapping\n- **GIVEN** a Kubernetes API server resolving the CRD type\n- **WHEN** the `TypeMeta` fields are inspected\n- **THEN** `APIVersion` is `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` and `Kind` is `AgentRuntime`\n\n#### Scenario: Resource plural matches client-go expectations\n- **GIVEN** a typed client for `AgentRuntime`\n- **WHEN** constructing a `GroupVersionResource` from the type","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-001/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775882734535,"end":1775882734554}}}}
